<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{{ report.ticker }} — Forensic Research Note · Muddy Reporter</title>

    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Source+Serif+4:opsz,wght@8..60,400;8..60,500;8..60,600;8..60,700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />

    <style>
      /* =========================================================
         PAGE / RESET — true investment-bank research-note layout
         ========================================================= */
      @page {
        size: A4 portrait;
        margin: 18mm 16mm 22mm;
      }
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --paper-deep: #f4f5f7;
        --paper-tint: #f8f9fb;
        --ink: #0a1f44;
        --ink-body: #1f2937;
        --ink-muted: #6b7280;
        --ink-dim: #9ca3af;
        --line: #e1e4e9;
        --line-strong: #cbd5e1;
        --navy: #0a1f44;
        --navy-deep: #061633;
        --gold: #b29869;
        --gold-deep: #9a8155;
        --good: #065f46;
        --good-bg: #f0fdf4;
        --good-line: #bbf7d0;
        --warn: #a16207;
        --warn-bg: #fefce8;
        --warn-line: #fde68a;
        --bad: #9b1c1c;
        --bad-bg: #fef2f2;
        --bad-line: #fecaca;
        --info: #1e40af;
        --info-bg: #eff6ff;
        --info-line: #bfdbfe;
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html, body {
        margin: 0; background: var(--paper); color: var(--ink-body);
        font-family: Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial;
        font-size: 11.5px; line-height: 1.55;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      }
      a { color: var(--navy); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line-strong); }
      a:hover { color: var(--navy-deep); border-bottom-color: var(--gold); }

      /* ============================================================
         RUNNING HEADER + FOOTER (visible on each printed page via
         position:fixed; on screen they sit at top/bottom of viewport
         but inside the doc frame to keep WYSIWYG)
         ============================================================ */
      .doc {
        max-width: 1024px;            /* on-screen container */
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 32px 60px;
      }

      .running-header {
        border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--ink);
        padding: 8px 0;
        display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted);
      }
      .running-header .left { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; }
      .running-header .brand-mono {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif;
        font-weight: 700; font-size: 12px; color: var(--navy);
        letter-spacing: 0;
      }
      .running-header .accent-dot { color: var(--gold); }
      .running-header .right { display: flex; gap: 16px; }
      .running-header .right span { color: var(--ink-body); }

      .gold-rule { height: 1px; background: var(--gold); margin: 0; }

      .toolbar {
        display: flex; justify-content: flex-end; gap: 8px;
        margin: 12px 0 8px;
      }
      .btn {
        background: var(--navy); color: #fff; border: 0;
        padding: 6px 12px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase;
        cursor: pointer; font-weight: 500;
      }
      .btn:hover { background: var(--navy-deep); }
      .btn.ghost { background: #fff; color: var(--navy); border: 1px solid var(--line-strong); }
      .btn.ghost:hover { background: var(--paper-deep); }

      /* ============================================================
         COVER BLOCK — title, ticker badge, sector chips, bottom line
         ============================================================ */
      .cover {
        padding: 18px 0 22px;
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--navy);
      }
      .cover-meta {
        display: flex; gap: 10px; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }
      .chip {
        display: inline-block; padding: 2px 8px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line-strong); background: var(--paper-deep);
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted); font-weight: 500;
      }
      .chip.gold { border-color: var(--gold); color: var(--gold-deep); background: rgba(178,152,105,0.06); }
      .chip.navy { border-color: var(--navy); color: var(--navy); background: rgba(10,31,68,0.04); }

      .cover-title {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif;
        font-weight: 700; font-size: 36px; line-height: 1.05;
        color: var(--navy); letter-spacing: -0.022em;
        margin: 4px 0 4px;
      }
      .cover-tagline {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif;
        font-style: italic; font-size: 16px; color: var(--ink-muted);
        line-height: 1.45;
        margin: 0 0 10px;
        max-width: 70%;
      }
      .cover-subline {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10.5px;
        letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: var(--ink-muted);
      }
      .cover-subline .v { color: var(--ink-body); }

      /* "Bottom line" callout — analyst's TL;DR at top, like a real note */
      .bottom-line {
        margin: 20px 0 0;
        border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
        background: #faf8f3;
        padding: 14px 18px;
      }
      .bottom-line .lab {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: 0.22em;
        color: var(--gold-deep); text-transform: uppercase;
        margin-bottom: 6px;
      }
      .bottom-line .body {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif;
        font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--ink-body);
      }

      /* ============================================================
         TWO-COLUMN BODY — main narrative left, key-data sidebar right
         (collapses to single column on print or narrow screen)
         ============================================================ */
      .two-col {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0,1fr) 260px;
        gap: 28px; margin-top: 24px;
      }
      @media (max-width: 760px) {
        .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      }
      @media print {
        .two-col { grid-template-columns: minmax(0,1fr) 200px; gap: 14px; }
      }

      .main-col { min-width: 0; }
      .side-col { min-width: 0; }

      .section {
        margin-top: 22px;
        page-break-inside: auto;
      }
      .section .sec-head {
        display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);
        padding-bottom: 4px; margin-bottom: 10px;
        page-break-after: avoid;
      }
      .sec-num {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold-deep);
      }
      .sec-title {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; color: var(--navy);
        font-weight: 700; font-size: 19px; letter-spacing: -0.012em;
        margin: 0;
      }
      .sec-sub {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-style: italic;
        color: var(--ink-muted); font-size: 11.5px;
        margin: 4px 0 0;
      }

      /* Generic prose */
      .prose { font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--ink-body); }
      .prose strong { color: var(--navy); }
      .prose ol, .prose ul { padding-left: 18px; margin: 6px 0 0; }
      .prose li { margin-bottom: 4px; }
      .muted { color: var(--ink-muted); }
      .small { font-size: 10.5px; }
      .mono { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }

      /* ============================================================
         SIDEBAR — Key Data, Top Concerns, Forensic Scores
         ============================================================ */
      .sidebox {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        background: #fff;
        margin-bottom: 14px;
        page-break-inside: avoid;
      }
      .sidebox .head {
        background: var(--navy); color: #fff;
        padding: 6px 10px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 9.5px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.20em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }
      .sidebox .head .gold-mark { color: var(--gold); }
      .sidebox .body { padding: 10px 12px; }

      .keydata {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
        row-gap: 6px; column-gap: 10px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 10.5px;
      }
      .keydata .k { color: var(--ink-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.10em; font-size: 9.5px; }
      .keydata .v { color: var(--navy); font-weight: 600; text-align: right; }
      .keydata .v.bad { color: var(--bad); }
      .keydata .v.warn { color: var(--warn); }
      .keydata .v.good { color: var(--good); }
      .keydata .row-divider { grid-column: 1 / -1; height: 1px; background: var(--line); margin: 2px 0; }

      .grade-display {
        display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between;
        padding: 6px 0;
      }
      .grade-letter {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 56px; line-height: 0.9; letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      }
      .grade-A { color: var(--good); }
      .grade-B { color: #4d7c0f; }
      .grade-C { color: var(--warn); }
      .grade-D { color: #b45309; }
      .grade-F { color: var(--bad); }

      .ml-banner {
        display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between;
        padding: 6px 0;
      }
      .ml-prob {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 38px; line-height: 0.9; letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      }
      .ml-prob.bad { color: var(--bad); }
      .ml-prob.warn { color: var(--warn); }
      .ml-prob.good { color: var(--good); }
      .pill-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 4px; margin-top: 8px; }

      .pill {
        display: inline-block; padding: 2px 7px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.10em; font-weight: 500;
        border: 1px solid var(--line-strong); color: var(--ink-muted);
        background: var(--paper-deep);
        text-transform: uppercase;
      }
      .pill.fact, .pill.high { color: var(--bad); border-color: var(--bad-line); background: var(--bad-bg); }
      .pill.inference, .pill.medium { color: var(--info); border-color: var(--info-line); background: var(--info-bg); }
      .pill.question, .pill.low { color: var(--warn); border-color: var(--warn-line); background: var(--warn-bg); }
      .pill.speculation { color: var(--bad); border-color: var(--bad-line); background: var(--bad-bg); }
      .pill.clean { color: var(--good); border-color: var(--good-line); background: var(--good-bg); }
      .pill.watch { color: var(--warn); border-color: var(--warn-line); background: var(--warn-bg); }
      .pill.suspicious, .pill.likely_fraud, .pill.likely_misrepresentation {
        color: var(--bad); border-color: var(--bad-line); background: var(--bad-bg);
      }
      .pill.agree { color: var(--good); border-color: var(--good-line); background: var(--good-bg); }
      .pill.disagree { color: var(--warn); border-color: var(--warn-line); background: var(--warn-bg); }

      /* Top concerns mini-list */
      .topconcerns ol {
        list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0;
        font-size: 10.5px; line-height: 1.45;
      }
      .topconcerns li {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 22px 1fr;
        gap: 4px; padding: 6px 0; border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--line);
      }
      .topconcerns li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
      .topconcerns .n {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--gold-deep); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1;
      }
      .topconcerns .t { color: var(--navy); font-weight: 600; }
      .topconcerns .t .pill { margin-left: 4px; }

      /* ============================================================
         FINDINGS — research-note style; numbered, dense
         ============================================================ */
      .finding {
        padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
        page-break-inside: avoid;
      }
      .finding:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
      .finding-head { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
      .finding .num {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--gold-deep); font-size: 22px; line-height: 1;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em; min-width: 32px;
      }
      .finding h4 {
        margin: 0; font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--navy); font-size: 15px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.25;
      }
      .finding .pills { margin: 4px 0 6px 42px; }
      .finding .body { margin-left: 42px; }
      .finding .why {
        border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
        background: #faf8f3; padding: 6px 12px; margin: 8px 0;
      }
      .finding .why .lab {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 8.5px; letter-spacing: 0.20em;
        color: var(--gold-deep); text-transform: uppercase;
      }

      .quote {
        white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 10.5px; color: var(--ink-body); line-height: 1.55;
        background: var(--paper-deep);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--navy);
        padding: 8px 12px; margin: 4px 0;
      }
      .cite {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px;
        word-break: break-all;
      }

      .subhead {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted); margin: 10px 0 4px;
      }

      /* ============================================================
         FULL-WIDTH BREAKOUTS — evidence ledger, financial tables,
         claims grid (escape the 2-col layout)
         ============================================================ */
      .breakout {
        margin: 26px 0;
        page-break-inside: auto;
      }

      table.tabular {
        width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10.5px;
      }
      table.tabular th {
        background: var(--paper-tint); color: var(--ink-muted);
        font-weight: 600; font-size: 9px;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase;
        text-align: right; padding: 7px 10px;
        border-bottom: 1.5px solid var(--navy);
      }
      table.tabular th:first-child { text-align: left; }
      table.tabular td {
        padding: 7px 10px; text-align: right;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      }
      table.tabular td:first-child { text-align: left; color: var(--navy); font-weight: 500; }
      table.tabular tbody tr:hover { background: var(--paper-tint); }

      table.ev-ledger {
        width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 10.5px;
      }
      table.ev-ledger th {
        background: var(--paper-tint); color: var(--ink-muted);
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase;
        text-align: left; padding: 8px 10px;
        border-bottom: 1.5px solid var(--navy);
      }
      table.ev-ledger td {
        padding: 10px; vertical-align: top;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      }
      table.ev-ledger tbody tr { page-break-inside: avoid; }
      table.ev-ledger tbody tr:hover { background: var(--paper-tint); }

      /* Anomaly card */
      .anomaly {
        border: 1px solid var(--line); padding: 12px 14px; margin-bottom: 8px;
        position: relative; background: #fff; page-break-inside: avoid;
      }
      .anomaly::before {
        content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; bottom: 0;
        width: 3px; background: var(--gold);
      }
      .anomaly h4 {
        margin: 0 0 4px; font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif;
        color: var(--navy); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600;
      }

      /* Two-col claim grid */
      .claim-row {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        border: 1px solid var(--line); margin-bottom: 8px;
        page-break-inside: avoid; background: #fff;
      }
      .claim-row > div { padding: 12px 14px; }
      .claim-row > div:first-child {
        border-right: 1px solid var(--line); background: var(--paper-deep);
      }
      .claim-row .role {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 8.5px;
        letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted); margin-bottom: 4px;
      }
      .claim-row .role.mgmt { color: var(--ink-muted); }
      .claim-row .role.counter { color: var(--bad); }

      /* Forensic score tiles row */
      .score-row {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
        gap: 8px; margin-top: 6px;
      }
      .score-tile {
        border: 1px solid var(--line); padding: 10px 12px;
        position: relative; background: #fff; page-break-inside: avoid;
      }
      .score-tile::before {
        content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; bottom: 0;
        width: 2px; background: var(--navy);
      }
      .score-tile .lab {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.20em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-muted);
      }
      .score-tile .num {
        font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif; font-weight: 700;
        font-size: 24px; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        margin: 4px 0; color: var(--navy);
      }
      .score-tile .num.bad { color: var(--bad); }
      .score-tile .num.warn { color: var(--warn); }
      .score-tile .num.good { color: var(--good); }
      .score-tile .note { font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--ink-muted); }

      /* Concerns by category — 2x2 grid */
      .cat-grid {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 10px;
      }
      .cat-card {
        border: 1px solid var(--line); padding: 10px 12px; background: #fff;
        page-break-inside: avoid;
      }
      .cat-card .lab {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: 0.20em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold-deep); margin-bottom: 4px;
      }
      .cat-card ul { padding-left: 16px; margin: 0; font-size: 11px; line-height: 1.55; }

      /* ============================================================
         DISCLAIMER FOOTER — like real research notes
         ============================================================ */
      .disclaimer {
        margin-top: 32px; padding-top: 16px;
        border-top: 2px solid var(--navy);
        font-size: 9.5px; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--ink-muted);
        page-break-before: auto;
      }
      .disclaimer h5 {
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--navy); margin: 0 0 6px;
      }
      .disclaimer p { margin: 0 0 6px; }
      .disclaimer .signoff {
        margin-top: 12px; padding-top: 8px;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
        display: flex; justify-content: space-between; gap: 16px;
        font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 9px;
        letter-spacing: 0.10em; text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--ink-dim);
      }

      /* ============================================================
         PRINT-ONLY: hide toolbar, force white, page-break controls
         ============================================================ */
      @media print {
        body { font-size: 10.5px; }
        .toolbar, .no-print { display: none !important; }
        .doc { padding: 0; max-width: none; }

        /* Each major section starts on a new page in print, except the cover */
        .section { page-break-inside: auto; }
        .breakout { page-break-inside: auto; }
        .finding { page-break-inside: avoid; }
        .anomaly, .claim-row, .cat-card, .sidebox, .score-tile { page-break-inside: avoid; }

        a { color: var(--navy); border: 0; }
        .running-header {
          position: fixed; top: 0; left: 16mm; right: 16mm;
          background: #fff;
        }

        /* Page numbers in the bottom margin */
        @page {
          @bottom-right {
            content: "Page " counter(page) " of " counter(pages);
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
            font-size: 8pt; color: #6b7280;
          }
          @bottom-left {
            content: "Muddy Reporter · Forensic Equity Research · {{ report.ticker }}";
            font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
            font-size: 8pt; color: #6b7280;
          }
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="doc">

      <!-- ============================================================
           RUNNING HEADER (institution / desk / ticker / date)
           ============================================================ -->
      <header class="running-header">
        <div class="left">
          <span class="brand-mono">Muddy Reporter <span class="accent-dot">·</span> Forensic Equity Research</span>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
          <span>{{ report.ticker }}</span>
          <span>{{ report.generated_at_iso[:10] if report.generated_at_iso else '' }}</span>
        </div>
      </header>
      <div class="gold-rule"></div>

      <div class="toolbar no-print">
        <button class="btn ghost" onclick="window.print()">Print / save PDF</button>
      </div>

      <!-- ============================================================
           COVER BLOCK — title, sector chips, bottom line
           ============================================================ -->
      <section class="cover">
        <div class="cover-meta">
          <span class="chip navy">Ticker · {{ report.ticker }}</span>
          <span class="chip">Concern thesis</span>
          <span class="chip">Public sources only</span>
          <span class="chip gold">Not investment advice</span>
        </div>

        <h1 class="cover-title">{{ report.company_name or report.ticker }}</h1>

        {% if report.snapshot.business_description %}
        <p class="cover-tagline">{{ report.snapshot.business_description }}</p>
        {% endif %}

        <div class="cover-subline">
          <span class="v">Issued {{ report.generated_at_iso }}</span>
          &nbsp;·&nbsp;
          <span>Engine</span> <span class="v">{{ report.provider_info.provider if report.provider_info else 'n/a' }}</span>
          (<span class="v">{{ report.provider_info.model if report.provider_info else 'n/a' }}</span>)
          &nbsp;·&nbsp;
          <span>Sources</span> <span class="v">{{ sources | length }} SEC filings + XBRL</span>
        </div>

        <div class="bottom-line">
          <div class="lab">Bottom line</div>
          <div class="body">{{ report.core_thesis or 'No thesis extracted.' }}</div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================================
           TWO-COLUMN BODY
           ============================================================ -->
      <div class="two-col">

        <!-- ====================== MAIN COLUMN ====================== -->
        <div class="main-col">

          <!-- 01 · COMPANY SNAPSHOT -->
          <section class="section">
            <div class="sec-head">
              <h2 class="sec-title">Company snapshot</h2>
              <span class="sec-num">01</span>
            </div>
            <div class="prose">
              {% if report.snapshot.where_it_operates %}<p><strong>Where it operates.</strong> {{ report.snapshot.where_it_operates }}</p>{% endif %}
              {% if report.snapshot.segments_or_revenue_model %}<p><strong>Revenue model / segments.</strong> {{ report.snapshot.segments_or_revenue_model }}</p>{% endif %}
              {% if report.snapshot.recent_corporate_actions %}<p><strong>Recent corporate actions.</strong> {{ report.snapshot.recent_corporate_actions }}</p>{% endif %}
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- 02 · CORE CONCERN THESIS (expanded) -->
          <section class="section">
            <div class="sec-head">
              <h2 class="sec-title">Why this name merits scrutiny</h2>
              <span class="sec-num">02 · Concern thesis</span>
            </div>
            <p class="prose" style="font-family:'Source Serif 4',serif; font-size:13px; line-height:1.7;">
              {{ report.core_thesis or '—' }}
            </p>
          </section>

          <!-- 03 · TOP RED FLAGS -->
          <section class="section">
            <div class="sec-head">
              <h2 class="sec-title">Top red flags</h2>
              <span class="sec-num">03 · Skeptical findings</span>
            </div>
            <p class="sec-sub">Each finding tagged with label (fact / inference / question / speculation), confidence, and a verbatim source citation. Independent verification required before acting.</p>
            {% for f in report.red_flags %}
            <div class="finding">
              <div class="finding-head">
                <span class="num">{{ "%02d"|format(loop.index) }}</span>
                <h4>{{ f.title }}</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="pills">
                <span class="pill {{ f.label }}">{{ f.label }}</span>
                <span class="pill {{ f.confidence }}">conf {{ f.confidence }}</span>
                <span class="pill">{{ f.category|replace('_',' ') }}</span>
              </div>
              <div class="body prose">
                <p><strong>Observation.</strong> {{ f.claim_or_observation }}</p>
                <div class="why">
                  <div class="lab">Why it matters</div>
                  <div style="margin-top:3px;">{{ f.why_it_matters }}</div>
                </div>

                {% if f.counterpoints_or_alt_explanations %}
                <div class="subhead">Counterpoints / alt. explanations</div>
                <ul>{% for c in f.counterpoints_or_alt_explanations %}<li>{{ c }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul>
                {% endif %}

                {% if f.open_questions %}
                <div class="subhead">Open questions</div>
                <ul>{% for q in f.open_questions %}<li>{{ q }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul>
                {% endif %}

                {% if f.citations %}
                <div class="subhead">Cited evidence</div>
                {% for ci in f.citations %}
                <div style="margin-bottom:6px;">
                  <a class="cite" href="{{ ci.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">{{ ci.doc_id }}</a>
                  <div class="quote">{{ ci.excerpt }}</div>
                </div>
                {% endfor %}
                {% else %}
                <div class="small muted" style="margin-top:6px;">No direct citation captured — treat as low-confidence pending verification.</div>
                {% endif %}
              </div>
            </div>
            {% endfor %}
          </section>

          <!-- 04 · OPEN QUESTIONS FOR MGMT -->
          <section class="section">
            <div class="sec-head">
              <h2 class="sec-title">Questions for management</h2>
              <span class="sec-num">04 · Diligence agenda</span>
            </div>
            {% if report.open_questions %}
            <ol class="prose">
              {% for q in report.open_questions %}<li>{{ q }}</li>{% endfor %}
            </ol>
            {% else %}
            <p class="prose muted">No questions extracted.</p>
            {% endif %}
          </section>

          <!-- 05 · CONCLUSION -->
          <section class="section">
            <div class="sec-head">
              <h2 class="sec-title">Conclusion</h2>
              <span class="sec-num">05 · Caution framing</span>
            </div>
            <p class="prose" style="font-family:'Source Serif 4',serif; font-size:13px; line-height:1.7;">
              {{ report.conclusion or '—' }}
            </p>
          </section>

        </div>

        <!-- ====================== SIDEBAR ====================== -->
        <aside class="side-col">

          <!-- KEY DATA panel (research-note style summary) -->
          <div class="sidebox">
            <div class="head">Key data <span class="gold-mark">·</span> at a glance</div>
            <div class="body">
              {% if report.risk_grade and report.risk_grade.grade %}
              <div class="grade-display">
                <div>
                  <div class="mono small muted" style="letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;font-size:9px;">Risk grade</div>
                  <span class="grade-letter grade-{{ report.risk_grade.grade }}">{{ report.risk_grade.grade }}</span>
                </div>
                <div style="text-align:right;">
                  <div class="mono small muted" style="letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;font-size:9px;">Score</div>
                  <div class="mono" style="font-size:18px;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy);">{{ report.risk_grade.score }}<span class="muted small" style="font-size:11px;">/100</span></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div style="height:1px;background:var(--line);margin:8px 0;"></div>
              {% endif %}

              {% if report.fraud_ensemble %}
              <div class="ml-banner">
                <div>
                  <div class="mono small muted" style="letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;font-size:9px;">Misrep risk</div>
                  <span class="ml-prob {% if (report.fraud_ensemble.combined_probability or 0) >= 0.7 %}bad{% elif (report.fraud_ensemble.combined_probability or 0) >= 0.45 %}warn{% else %}good{% endif %}">{{ "%.0f"|format((report.fraud_ensemble.combined_probability or 0) * 100) }}%</span>
                </div>
                <span class="pill {{ report.fraud_ensemble.verdict|replace('likely_misrepresentation','likely_fraud') }}">{{ (report.fraud_ensemble.verdict or 'watch')|replace('_',' ') }}</span>
              </div>
              <div class="pill-row">
                {% if report.fraud_ensemble.agreement %}<span class="pill {{ report.fraud_ensemble.agreement }}">models {{ report.fraud_ensemble.agreement }}</span>{% endif %}
              </div>
              <div style="height:1px;background:var(--line);margin:10px 0 6px;"></div>
              {% endif %}

              <div class="keydata">
                <div class="k">Filings analyzed</div><div class="v">{{ sources | length }}</div>
                <div class="k">Red flags</div><div class="v {% if (report.red_flags|length) >= 5 %}bad{% elif (report.red_flags|length) >= 1 %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.red_flags | length }}</div>
                <div class="k">Quant anomalies</div><div class="v {% if (report.financial_anomalies|length) >= 3 %}bad{% elif (report.financial_anomalies|length) >= 1 %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.financial_anomalies | length }}</div>
                <div class="k">Open questions</div><div class="v">{{ report.open_questions | length }}</div>
                <div class="k">Mgmt claims tested</div><div class="v">{{ report.management_claims_vs_counterpoints | length }}</div>
                <div class="k">Evidence rows</div><div class="v">{{ report.evidence_summary | length }}</div>

                {% if report.forensic_scores %}
                <div class="row-divider"></div>
                {% if report.forensic_scores.beneish_m is not none %}
                <div class="k">Beneish M</div><div class="v {% if report.forensic_scores.beneish_signal == 'manipulator' %}bad{% else %}good{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.beneish_m }}</div>
                {% endif %}
                {% if report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f is not none %}
                <div class="k">Piotroski F</div><div class="v {% if report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f >= 7 %}good{% elif report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f <= 3 %}bad{% else %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f }}/9</div>
                {% endif %}
                {% if report.forensic_scores.altman_z is not none %}
                <div class="k">Altman Z'</div><div class="v {% if report.forensic_scores.altman_zone == 'distress' %}bad{% elif report.forensic_scores.altman_zone == 'safe' %}good{% else %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.altman_z }}</div>
                {% endif %}
                {% endif %}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- TWO-MODEL BREAKDOWN -->
          {% if report.fraud_ensemble and report.fraud_ensemble.votes %}
          <div class="sidebox">
            <div class="head">Two-model ensemble</div>
            <div class="body">
              <div class="keydata">
                <div class="k" style="grid-column:1/-1;font-size:8.5px;">LLM Few-Shot ({{ report.provider_info.model if report.provider_info else 'n/a' }})</div>
                <div class="k">Probability</div><div class="v">{{ "%.0f"|format(((report.fraud_ensemble.votes.llm_few_shot.probability) or 0) * 100) }}%</div>
                <div class="k">Verdict</div><div class="v">{{ (report.fraud_ensemble.votes.llm_few_shot.verdict or '—')|replace('_',' ') }}</div>
                <div class="k">Confidence</div><div class="v">{{ report.fraud_ensemble.votes.llm_few_shot.confidence or '—' }}</div>
                <div class="row-divider"></div>
                <div class="k" style="grid-column:1/-1;font-size:8.5px;">Logistic regression (9 features)</div>
                <div class="k">Probability</div><div class="v">{{ "%.0f"|format(((report.fraud_ensemble.votes.ml_logreg.probability) or 0) * 100) }}%</div>
                <div class="k">Verdict</div><div class="v">{{ (report.fraud_ensemble.votes.ml_logreg.verdict or '—')|replace('_',' ') }}</div>
                <div class="k">Coverage</div><div class="v">{{ "%.0f"|format((report.fraud_ensemble.votes.ml_logreg.coverage or 0) * 100) }}%</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endif %}

          <!-- TOP CONCERNS mini-list (first 5 red flags) -->
          {% if report.red_flags %}
          <div class="sidebox topconcerns">
            <div class="head">Top concerns</div>
            <div class="body">
              <ol>
                {% for f in report.red_flags[:5] %}
                <li>
                  <span class="n">{{ loop.index }}</span>
                  <span><span class="t">{{ f.title }}</span><span class="pill {{ f.label }}" style="margin-left:4px;">{{ f.label }}</span></span>
                </li>
                {% endfor %}
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endif %}

          <!-- SOURCES sidebar -->
          {% if sources %}
          <div class="sidebox">
            <div class="head">Sources analyzed</div>
            <div class="body">
              <ul style="padding-left:14px;margin:0;font-size:10px;line-height:1.5;">
                {% for s in sources %}
                <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">
                  <span class="mono" style="color:var(--navy);font-weight:600;">{{ s.filing_type }}</span>
                  <span class="mono muted">· {{ s.filing_date or 'undated' }}</span><br/>
                  <a class="cite" href="{{ s.primary_url }}" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">{{ s.doc_id }}</a>
                </li>
                {% endfor %}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          {% endif %}

        </aside>
      </div>

      <!-- ============================================================
           FULL-WIDTH BREAKOUT: QUANT ANOMALIES
           ============================================================ -->
      {% if report.financial_anomalies %}
      <section class="breakout section">
        <div class="sec-head">
          <h2 class="sec-title">Quantitative anomalies</h2>
          <span class="sec-num">06 · Deterministic XBRL detector</span>
        </div>
        <p class="sec-sub">Rule-based pattern checks against filed XBRL data. No LLM in this layer.</p>
        {% for a in report.financial_anomalies %}
        <div class="anomaly">
          <h4>{{ a.title }}</h4>
          <div style="margin:4px 0 6px;">
            <span class="pill {{ a.severity }}">{{ a.severity }}</span>
            <span class="pill">{{ a.category }}</span>
            <span class="pill">{{ a.metric }}</span>
          </div>
          <div class="prose small">{{ a.description }}</div>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </section>
      {% endif %}

      <!-- ============================================================
           FULL-WIDTH BREAKOUT: FORENSIC MODELS
           ============================================================ -->
      {% if report.forensic_scores %}
      <section class="breakout section">
        <div class="sec-head">
          <h2 class="sec-title">Academic forensic models</h2>
          <span class="sec-num">07 · Beneish · Piotroski · Altman</span>
        </div>
        <div class="score-row">
          {% if report.forensic_scores.beneish_m is not none %}
          <div class="score-tile">
            <div class="lab">Beneish M-Score</div>
            <div class="num {% if report.forensic_scores.beneish_signal == 'manipulator' %}bad{% else %}good{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.beneish_m }}</div>
            <div class="note">Threshold M &gt; -1.78 = likely manipulator (Beneish 1999).</div>
          </div>
          {% endif %}
          {% if report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f is not none %}
          <div class="score-tile">
            <div class="lab">Piotroski F-Score</div>
            <div class="num {% if report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f >= 7 %}good{% elif report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f <= 3 %}bad{% else %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.piotroski_f }}<span class="muted" style="font-size:14px;">/9</span></div>
            <div class="note">Nine binary tests of fundamental strength (Piotroski 2000).</div>
          </div>
          {% endif %}
          {% if report.forensic_scores.altman_z is not none %}
          <div class="score-tile">
            <div class="lab">Altman Z'-Score</div>
            <div class="num {% if report.forensic_scores.altman_zone == 'distress' %}bad{% elif report.forensic_scores.altman_zone == 'safe' %}good{% else %}warn{% endif %}">{{ report.forensic_scores.altman_z }}</div>
            <div class="note">Zone: {{ report.forensic_scores.altman_zone or 'gray' }}. (Altman 1968 / 1983 private-firm variant.)</div>
          </div>
          {% endif %}
        </div>
      </section>
      {% endif %}

      <!-- ============================================================
           FULL-WIDTH BREAKOUT: EVIDENCE LEDGER
           ============================================================ -->
      {% if report.evidence_summary %}
      <section class="breakout section">
        <div class="sec-head">
          <h2 class="sec-title">Evidence ledger</h2>
          <span class="sec-num">08 · Tied to source documents</span>
        </div>
        <p class="sec-sub">One row per cited excerpt. Sorted by evidence strength: facts first, then inferences, then open questions.</p>
        <table class="ev-ledger">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th style="width:7%;">Label</th>
              <th style="width:32%;">Finding</th>
              <th style="width:18%;">Source filing</th>
              <th>Cited excerpt</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {% for r in report.evidence_summary %}
            <tr>
              <td>
                <span class="pill {{ r.label }}">{{ r.label }}</span>
                <div class="small muted" style="margin-top:3px;">{{ r.confidence }}</div>
              </td>
              <td>
                <div style="font-weight:600;color:var(--navy);font-size:11px;">{{ r.finding_title }}</div>
                {% if r.category %}<div class="small muted mono" style="margin-top:3px;">{{ r.category|replace('_',' ') }}</div>{% endif %}
                {% if r.why_it_matters %}<div class="small" style="margin-top:4px;">{{ r.why_it_matters }}</div>{% endif %}
              </td>
              <td class="cite">
                {% if r.url %}
                <a href="{{ r.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">{{ r.filing_type or 'filing' }} · {{ r.filing_date or '' }}</a>
                {% elif r.missing_citation %}
                <span class="muted small">— no source cited —</span>
                {% else %}
                <span class="muted small">{{ r.filing_type or 'unknown' }}</span>
                {% endif %}
              </td>
              <td>
                {% if r.excerpt %}
                <div class="quote" style="margin:0;">{{ r.excerpt }}</div>
                {% else %}
                <span class="muted small">No excerpt captured</span>
                {% endif %}
              </td>
            </tr>
            {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>
      {% endif %}

      <!-- ============================================================
           FULL-WIDTH BREAKOUT: MGMT CLAIMS vs COUNTERPOINTS
           ============================================================ -->
      {% if report.management_claims_vs_counterpoints %}
      <section class="breakout section">
        <div class="sec-head">
          <h2 class="sec-title">Management claims vs counterpoints</h2>
          <span class="sec-num">09 · Tested against the filings</span>
        </div>
        {% for row in report.management_claims_vs_counterpoints %}
        <div class="claim-row">
          <div>
            <div class="role mgmt">Management</div>
            <div class="prose small">{{ row.claim }}</div>
            {% if row.source_excerpt %}<div class="quote" style="margin-top:6px;">{{ row.source_excerpt }}</div>{% endif %}
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="role counter">Counterpoint / inconsistency</div>
            <div class="prose small">{{ row.counterpoint }}</div>
            <div style="margin-top:6px;">
              <span class="pill {{ row.confidence }}">conf {{ row.confidence }}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </section>
      {% endif %}

      <!-- ============================================================
           FULL-WIDTH BREAKOUT: CONCERNS BY CATEGORY
           ============================================================ -->
      {% if report.concerns_by_category %}
      <section class="breakout section">
        <div class="sec-head">
          <h2 class="sec-title">Concerns by category</h2>
          <span class="sec-num">10 · Accounting · Governance · Disclosure · Operations</span>
        </div>
        <div class="cat-grid">
          {% for cat, items in report.concerns_by_category.items() %}
          <div class="cat-card">
            <div class="lab">{{ cat|replace('_',' ') }}</div>
            {% if items %}<ul>{% for it in items %}<li>{{ it }}</li>{% endfor %}</ul>
            {% else %}<div class="small muted">No specific concerns extracted.</div>{% endif %}
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </section>
      {% endif %}

      <!-- ============================================================
           FULL-WIDTH BREAKOUT: ANNUAL FINANCIALS
           ============================================================ -->
      {% if report.financial_table %}
      <section class="breakout section">
        <div class="sec-head">
          <h2 class="sec-title">Annual financials</h2>
          <span class="sec-num">11 · XBRL · last seven fiscal years</span>
        </div>
        <table class="tabular">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Year</th><th>Revenue</th><th>Net income</th><th>CFO</th>
              <th>AR</th><th>Inventory</th><th>Goodwill</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {% macro fnum(v) -%}
              {% if v is none or v is undefined %}—{% else %}{{ "{:,.0f}".format(v) }}{% endif %}
            {%- endmacro %}
            {% for row in report.financial_table %}
            <tr>
              <td>{{ row.year }}</td>
              <td>{{ fnum(row.get('revenue')) }}</td>
              <td>{{ fnum(row.get('net_income')) }}</td>
              <td>{{ fnum(row.get('operating_cash_flow')) }}</td>
              <td>{{ fnum(row.get('accounts_receivable')) }}</td>
              <td>{{ fnum(row.get('inventory')) }}</td>
              <td>{{ fnum(row.get('goodwill')) }}</td>
            </tr>
            {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p class="small muted" style="margin-top:6px;">Values in reporting-currency units as filed. Blanks indicate the concept was not tagged in that period.</p>
      </section>
      {% endif %}

      <!-- ============================================================
           DISCLAIMER & METHODOLOGY (last page)
           ============================================================ -->
      <section class="disclaimer">
        <h5>Methodology &amp; limitations</h5>
        {% if report.limitations %}
        <ul style="padding-left:18px;margin:0 0 8px;">
          {% for l in report.limitations %}<li>{{ l }}</li>{% endfor %}
        </ul>
        {% endif %}
        <p>This document is a <strong style="color:var(--navy);">concern thesis</strong> generated by an automated forensic-research prototype, not investment advice and not an allegation of wrongdoing. Every claim is graded for confidence (fact / inference / question / speculation) and tied to a verbatim citation. Independent verification against the cited filings is required before acting on any finding.</p>
        <p>The misrepresentation-risk percentage shown above is the average of two independent estimators &mdash; an LLM few-shot classifier (DeepSeek V4 Pro / Gemini 2.5) and a deterministic logistic-regression model trained on a curated set of historical fraud/control cases &mdash; weighted by each model's confidence and coverage. A reading of <em>disagree</em> means the two models reached different verdicts and the combined number should be treated with extra caution.</p>

        <div class="signoff">
          <span>© Muddy Reporter Prototype · Case-study build</span>
          <span>{{ report.ticker }} · generated {{ report.generated_at_iso }}</span>
        </div>
      </section>

    </main>
  </body>
</html>
